op chips could scale up to 24 cores and 48 threads. There’s even speculation around 32 or 64-core configurations if AMD chooses to push into extreme desktop territory.</p> <p>The chips are expected to land in mid to late 2026, roughly in line with Intel’s planned Nova Lake-S launch. Whether Zen 6 keeps AMD in pole position for gaming and multi-threaded performance or simply maintains a solid lead remains to be seen, but the foundations are clearly already in place.</p></div>	2025-07-11 07:58:34	nick [AT] fudzilla [DOT] com (Nick Farrell)	f	2025-07-14 04:31:36.150014
